  "text": "For sequential data where elements are connected by linear structures, a sequence kernel has been constructed based on subsequences [CITATION_1] . The algorithm is based on dynamic programming, and can be computed in quadratic time. A simpler but more efficient kernel called the spectrum kernel uses (contiguous) substrings and can be computed in linear time [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The spectrum kernel with gaps [CITATION_4] was proposed as an intermediate variation of these two string kernels.",
